<br>
Boosting Strength<br>
I noticed that Carrier Crafts are both cheap to buy and relativly easy to use (low req's), and they boost strength. A ql 50 Craft was reported to take 80 in vehicle ground and give a 50 boost to strength. Can one use theese to meet implant and armour req's? Implants are maybe the most interesting part, but impossible because the vehicle can't be used in shops...?<br>
<br>
Zalcroi (very much looking forward to his return) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucrimhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crimhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Martial, Baby, MARTIAL.</span><br>  Posts: 412<br> <font color=#660000>(9/3/02 9:12:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2121.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BwT, Pulling and boosting strength.</span><hr size=1> Don't know about bows or carrier crafts, but as far as BWT is concerned......You can no longer buy BWT in any store. It is all mission reward or dropped in missions. The lowest ql BWT is ql 50, so unless you are in a team that can do missions way above thier lvl don't expect to gt one until you are in your mid 30s or higher (assuming of course that you can do solo missions 15-20 lvls higher than your current lvl). Hope it helps.<br>
